The paper discusses data privacy and anonymization techniques in the context of enterprise data management, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the potential for adversarial attacks using information fusion techniques, which could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes a solution to address the problem of fusion-resilient enterprise data anonymization, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CY).
